Review text: Very nice ambiance. Internet speed is very decent. There is long table for you to work in group. Barista is very kind. Parking could ve difficult. Accepting cashless payment.

Housed in the new refurbished Post Bloc - a formerly state-owned post office in a Colonial heritage setting - the popular coffee joint will gonna be packed by the observers and passers-by. Don't forget to peruse and browse the hip tenants inside to add your IG reels and stories.

This cafe is located in the very central of Jakarta. The building is vintage and tje interior is homy enough.
The menu is the same with other starbuck's cafes, the plus from this cafe is the location, close to the Monas, Pasar Senen, Lapangan Banteng and the National Mosque Istiqlal, the Philately Museum, the Cathedral, Pintu Air Commuterline station, etc.
Nice place stop wheb you're around Central Jakarta
The air con is not too cold, maybe because the place quite crowded, service good as starbucks standard

One of the best Starbucks outlets in town. Loved the location and how well-spaced it is between the tables. Morning is the best time to visit here, nice window lights and cozy ambience for both relaxing or discussing some ideas with friends.
Cozy place to hang out with Friends
Great place to hang out . Quite spacious. The staff are friendly and helpful

Its a starbucks in a heritage building, the batavia colonial post office.
Its very cozy inside, with interiors dominated by wood and individual sofas which is plush enough. Sadly, there's no information about history of the place.
Expect the usual drinks and light bites from starbucks, but the service could be improved more. The barista team on duty seems impatient
Starbucks is always a nice place to chill out wherever it is...
Nice architecture & interior .. bicycle riders friendly..

This Starbucks is pretty cozy, it's true its located near a crowded street just across the pasar baru market, but inside we almost cant hear what happen outside, the music is also not too loud, unlike many starbucks out there, and what amaze me most js its scebery from the window, there are still tree, so it is calming, oh yeah im forgot bout the coffee, but what the heck, its starbucks coffee you know what you paid for, and for this oerfect ambience the hell with coffee..
Nice place, cozy, and good coffee
Classic building and nice ambience. The place is so quiet and they serve good coffee tho. Best place for hang out or work.
Nice ambiance, quite spacious and cozy. Nice place to sketch and enjoying your "me time".
Such a nice place to have your work done. It has Mushalla also.

Located in one section of the old Post Office building, this Starbucks outlet used to be my ideal go to morning breakfast since they open early. However, since the Post Bloc opened last September 2021, parking has been a nightmare wince you have to park illegally on street next to Gedung Kesenian Jakartaband risk yourself in being towed and pay Rp. 500.000 towing fine.
The Starbucks itself is fine ... the parking is not. Starbucks should talk to management of Post Bloc about this, since it definitely affects their customers.
I will choose to drink and eat outside since when you come at night, you will have a nice view and nice place to talk while drinking your coffee.

A special Starbucks experience. Service good, coffee {i had latte} by barista seems better than the last one I tried at Chinatown. Old colonial building so ambience is good. High ceiling. Plug points plenty at seating area if you need to charge anything.

Their services are great like all Starbucks standard services around the world. The ambience is good. It's cozy and convenient to hang out with friends or do some work stuff here with your laptop while sip some nice drinks and snacks. Recommended to visit here.

Nice place and nice service, the place quite big and have great designed store for relax or meet up with business partner. The place quite strategies between school and busway. But i have bad experience in parking area, too expensive for "parkir liar" or unauthorized parking. I recommend this place for relax and enjoying coffee.
a nice place to hangout in Central Jakarta

A good place for hangouts and having coffee's. Best fully services. Stand in old building. Open early in the morning at 6.30 Am to 10 Pm Sunday to Thursday,  6.30 Am to 11.00 Pm, Friday to Sunday. Toilet area and Prayer room is available. Less parking space.
Modern coffee with classic building, love it..  . This's not mainstream
One of the best Starbucks I ever been to in Jakarta. Love the place, the vintage feeling of the bulding fits perfectly with the decoration.
My fav coffee shop starbucks. Always enjoyed sitting here.
Great place for working, not crowded. Unfortunately the WiFi provided is an unsecured network, better to use mobile tethered network

Nice cozy place located in a historic old building in the heart of the city. This heritage building was constructed between 1912-1929, and was originally the building of the Dutch colonial government's post office. Personally not a big fan of the coffee at this particular coffee chain but it seems to be the only decent coffee shop nearby Borobudur hotel. Stars are strictly for the location only.

Nice place to enjoy the coffie and you can also working from here.
Have a lot table and follow the protocol.
Have a space for pray (sholat). Nice service and have a space for parking.

Nice place but always get annoyed by how the barista keep offering you soy milk, extra caramel sauce, or sumatran coffee choice when all you need is a cup of freaking coffee. I know they get additional revenue but most of the time you're in a rush and they really didn't get it. God sake!
Good service good ambience and more important good coffee

Located next to Pasar Baru post office, this Starbucks Filateli ambience is very convenient and relaxing. Not as crowded as the other chain stores, this place is good to hang out with friend, talking gossips and catch up new life stories.

Love the place!
Located in an old post office building, it has a colonial look with high ceiling and narrow tall windows and whitewashed wall.
Food and drinks are typical of that big coffee shop chain, merchandise are also available.
The smoking rooms are in two areas, front and left side, they are uncomfortable during the day what with the equator humidity.
Toilets are in the back area, through a swing door out into a small garden with a memento from the past^^
Nice Starbucks outlet. Great for working and chilling
Decaf caramel machiato with raspberry syrup always be my fav. Love the ambience in Sbux Filateli, Juanda. Good place to chill
Fresh coffee. Nice service. Don't forget wear your mask!

Classic Ambience, regular Starbucks drinks, the vibe is what really makes this place different.

a good rendezvous spot after morning walk/jog because it within reach from Lapangan Banteng (Banteng square). this is also my first time during Ramadan, so it had less visitors. the only setback is some table are left uncleaned after use. Nice place. Comfy. Pelayanan super cepat. Very limited seats tho

Do you like coffee? Do you like historica and fancy building? Love to hang out around central Jakarta? Then this place prolly will suit you. Nice as any Starbucks can be. This place is just perfect. Just dont forget to use a face mask during visiting.
Nice place, but parking space is limited relative to shop size
Located inside a recently-restored colonial building, this Starbucks is definitely one of the most unique Starbucks outlets in Jakarta.

Modern and vintage, all in one. This place is a great example of the importance of maintaining the exterior of a building. Very clean interior and cozy enough for anyone to spend the whole entire day sipping on delicious Starbucks coffee. Even though it's a suitable place to meet up with clients, you should avoid it as parking is almost impossible to find. But the best part is, you can cross the street and have a great meal at Pasar Baru, assuming you still have money left from an overpriced Starbucks frappucino.

THE PARKING IS NOT GOOD, EXPENSIVE AND NOT FRIENDLY AT ALL. Actually the drinks, beverages, baristas and place are all so good, met the starbucks standard. Even the praying room for moslem is available inside. So, you better use the public transport like taxi or gojek/grab to go there.
